      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your eye symptoms sound like a classic case of conjunctivitis, which can be caused by a variety of factors, including bacteria, viruses, or allergens. The discharge and redness are signs that you should not ignore. I recommend you use a warm compress to soothe the irritation and apply a few drops of antibiotic eye drops that are available over-the-counter, such as Polymyxin B Sulfate and Trimethoprim, to help clear up the infection. Make sure to follow the dosage instructions on the bottle. If symptoms persist, consider visiting a healthcare professional. Remember, it's always better to err on the side of caution when it comes to your health.",
